							<p>Using the Web Evaluation Checklist and the information from the Berkeley site, try evaluating sites that have information about one of the following topics that are complex and have many sides:</p>


<ul class="circle">							<li>Children's immunizations or children's shots</li>
							<li>Cell phone dangers</li>
							<li>Red light cameras</li>
							<li>Evolution theory</li>
							<li>Climate change</li>

</ul>
<hr>							<p>Go to <a href="http://google.com">http://google.com</a> and enter one of the search topics listed above. Looking at the URLs,
								select two sites to review, one that seems credible and one that might be biased.</p>
							<p>Remember, you will be evaluating the site that provides the information not the information itself. Fill out the Web Evaluation Checklist for each site. You may not be able to complete all portions of the checklist for both sites and if you can't, that should tell you something about the site.</p>
